  "text": "The result of the baseline measurements are given in Tables  1 and 2 . The VO 2 max values in L/min and ml/min/kg lean body mass were not significantly different (pϭ0.12 and 0.20, respectively) between the two groups, closely matching those predicted for sedentary and healthy men of the same age, taking into account the higher VO 2 max values on treadmill vs. cycle ergometer [CITATION_1] . However, a higher fitness level for nonsmokers was indicated by the significantly lower resting HR and %fat and higher VO 2 max expressed as ml/min/kg wt. The lean body mass did not differ significantly between groups. No significant difference between groups was noted in resting SBP, DBP or exercise HR ( Table 2 ). The HbCO in smokers was significantly higher by 5.1%. Although the difference in Hb concentration and Hb/Hct ratio was not significant between groups, the smokers' Hct was significantly higher.",
